etymologies: mid 19th century: from Greek teleos ‘complete’ + osteon ‘bone’

definitions: a fish of a large group that comprises all ray-finned fishes apart from the primitive bichirs, sturgeons, paddlefishes, freshwater garfishes, and bowfins.

notes.text: Division (or infraclass) Teleostei, subclass Actinopterygii: many orders

shortDefinitions: fish of large group that comprises all ray-finned fishes apart from primitive bichirs
